# HOI4 Modding

These rules are derived from HOI4 Agent Skill. If `skill/hoi4-modding/` exists in this workspace, treat it as canonical. Otherwise, follow this adapter.

Treat HOI4 mods as Paradox data-script projects. Before editing, inspect the mod root, descriptor files, nearby conventions, prefixes, namespaces, localization files, and affected systems.

Prefer small loadable edits. Add localization for visible text. Match event IDs to namespaces. Check scopes for triggers and effects. Verify focus references, event calls, idea references, and GFX references.

When debugging, read `error.log` before guessing. Fix parse errors before logic errors.

Do not edit vanilla installation files directly or copy proprietary HOI4/DLC assets into the repository.

Do not claim in-game validation unless HOI4 was actually launched and tested.
